{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Stochastic weight averaging (SWA) shows that combining weights from multiple checkpoints of the same model improves performance (Izmailov et al., 2018; Guo et al., 2023).",
    "By averaging points along a training trajectory, SWA benefits from mode connectivity (Draxler et al., 2018; Garipov et al., 2018; Kuditipudi et al., 2019; Benton et al., 2021), i.ei.",
    "the observation that distinct optima are linked by low-loss paths.",
    "Thus, model variants sharing an optimization trajectory can be interpolated with negligible performance loss (Frankle et al., 2020).",
    "Robustness to small weight perturbations further supports such combinations (Arora et al., 2018)."
  ],
